    <div class = "getting started" > 
        <h3>Getting Started </h3>
            <hr style = "border: 0.5px solid black;"/> 
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "extras" >
        <h3>Extras</h3>
        
        <p> 
            For information about product and help, you can use our layout tabs on the to left of the Web Application, bottom Mobile Application). There are <strong>FAQ, Contuct Us, and Product Features</strong>.
        </p>
            <a href="screenshots/umpic%20-%20Copy.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/umpic%20-%20Copy.png" /> </a>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "download/access">
        <h3>Downloading and Accessing Website</h3>
        
        <p>
            To access the control and data/information displays, you need to download the mobile application for android. For web application, access browser.<em><strong>Needs Internet Access.</strong></em>
        </p> 
                <a href="screenshots/umpic.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/umpic.png" /> </a>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "sign in/sign up">
        <h3>Signing Up and Signing In</h3>
        
        <p>Here you will create an account with your specified information. (If account has already been created proceed to <strong>Step 2</strong>). </p>
            <a href="screenshots/Designpt1-susi.png">   <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/Designpt1-susi.png" /></a>
        
        <p>1. Input your e-mail and password on the specified lines accordingly. Input your password one more time for any mismatch. 
        </p>
            <a href="screenshots/Of8f8.png">    <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/Of8f8.png" /></a>

        <p>2. Click <Strong>Sign In</Strong>. Input your e-mail and password. Press <strong>Enter</strong>.
        </p>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "account"> 
        <h3>Acccount</h3> 
        
        <p>With an accessed <strong> Account</strong> you gain access on to functions of <strong>Register Lawn, Abort, Data Vizualization, Water Lawn, and Settings</strong> accordingly. Clicking <strong>Water Lawn</strong> will automatically water lawn. (NOTE: For Mobile Applications, look under <strong>Control</strong> for <strong>Abort</strong> function).
        </p>
        
            <a href="screenshots/Designpt1%20-%20Copy.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/Designpt1%20-%20Copy.png" /> </a>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "register">
        <h3>Registering Lawn</h3>
    
        <p>Once having acceses to account you click <strong>Register Lawn</strong>. Then from the <strong>Register Lawn</strong> page you can choose from the following to modify for your needs: 
        </p>
            <a href="screenshots/reglawn.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/reglawn.png"/> </a>

        <p>1. <strong>Charging and Storage </strong>. (Here you put your location of the charging station and storage of drone).</p> 
    
        <p>2. <strong>Dimensions</strong> (Here you modify your lawn dimensions to your preference).</p>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "settings">
        <h3>Settings</h3>
        
        <p> This tab is located on your <strong>Account</strong> page and you will <strong>Add Drone</strong>, change your <strong>Scheduling</strong>, and change your<strong>Username/Password</strong>
        </p>
            <a href="screenshots/Designpt1%20-%20Sett.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/Designpt1%20-%20Sett.png"/> </a>
    </div>
    
    
    <div class = "webapp"></div>
        <h3>FOR WEB APPLICATION ONLY</h3> 
            <hr style = "border: 0.5px solid black;"/>
    
    
    <div class = "data"></div>
        <h3>Data Vizualization</h3>
    
        <p>To access and view <strong>Water Amount, Water Saved, and Power Consumption</strong> you go to our Data Vizualization display on your account page. (NOTE: Water Amount displayed in Gal/Min).
        </p>
            <a href="screenshots/data.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/data.png"/>
            </a>
    
    <div class = "mobapp"></div>
        <h3>FOR MOBILE APPLICATION ONLY</h3> 
            <hr style = "border: 0.5px solid black;"/>
    
    
    <div class = "control"></div>
        <h3>Control</h3>
    
            <a href="screenshots/designpt2.png"> <img alt="A screenshot showing CSS Quick Edit" src="screenshots/designpt2.png"/>
            </a>
    
        <p>For your control functions you are given 3 options when clicked: </p> 
    
        <p>1. <strong>Abort</strong>. Press when drone has become disfunctional.</p>
    
        <p>2. <strong>Manual</strong> Override. Only use under <em>certain</em> circumstances. </p>
    
        <p>3. <strong>Return to base and/or refill</strong>. </p>
    
